  <description><![CDATA[<p>You know it's good when it's popular with the locals - Kamnik is only 35 minutes from Ljubljana airport, but feels worlds away thanks to the pristine nature, medieval architecture and local traditions. </p>
<h3>Holidays in Kamnik</h3>
<p>One of the most beautiful medieval towns in Slovenia, Kamnik was once a thriving trade town and used to be surrounded by high walls and a moat. Now you'll get lost in its rich history and medieval architecture - the prettiest street in town is Šutna which is lined with traditional signboards and remnants of old crafts and tradespeople. Discover architectural highlights of the town like the pretty chapel at Mali Grad Hill - the last remaining part of an 11th Century Castle. Or the old castle remains at Stari Grad - the views from this panoramic spot stretch for miles on a clear day.</p>
<h3>Kamnik-Savinja Alps: a hiker's paradise</h3>
<p>Lace up your walking boots and get ready to discover ancient mountain pastures, hidden valleys, castle remnants and secret peaks - this is a paradise for exploring on foot. Take a leisurely stroll around the Volčji Potok Arboretum with its thousands of plant and tree species, or escape into nature on the path along the <span>Kamniška Bistrica River. For a breathe of mountain air, head to Velika Planina - one of the most beautiful Alpine pastures in Slovenia, dotted with traditional shepherd's huts. Keen hiker's should follow in the footsteps of the locals - l</span>ike every Slovenian should visit Mount Triglav (the highest peak in Slovenia) at least once in their lives, everyone from Kamnik should visit the Kamnik Saddle - the dip in the mountains between the peaks of Brana and Planjava in the Kamnik-Savinja. </p>
<h3>Kamnik cuisine</h3>
<p>With its rich history and culture, it's no surprise that Kamnik is known for its food and drink. Trnič hard cheese is a must-try - it's from the Velika Planina plateau and is a traditional symbol of love that shepherd's would give to their partner at the end of summer. Sample some local Slovenian food at the Mili Vrh guesthouse just outside Kamnik, and you can try trout from the Tuhinja valley prepared in 10 different ways at the Terme Snovik's own Potočka restaurant. Slovenia is known for its wine, but beer lovers will really love Kamnik - there a four brewery's nearby including the Mali Grad brewery which is the oldest in Kamnik and the Maister brewery which started out with a group of friends home-brewing beer and got out of control.</p>
<h3>Stay at Slovenia's highest spa resort</h3>
<p>There's nothing better than a bit of relaxation after a long walk, and the Terme Snovik is just the ticket. Relax in the thermal indoor and outdoor pools - the water comes from deep in the Earth and is naturally rich in minerals like calcium and magnesium. Sooth achy calves and feet with Kneipp, head to the saunas or treat yourself to a massage.</p>
<h2>Why book a summer holiday to Kamnik with Inghams?</h2>
<p>At Inghams, we do walking holidays differently. With no fixed itinerary, you have more time in your destination and the freedom to walk as much or as little as you like, discovering some of Kamnik's best walking routes and activities at your own pace.</p>
<p>With over 85 years of outdoor travel experience, our holiday packages to Kamnik include flights, transfers, and accommodation, so you can relax and leave the small details to us. Our experts can help you choose the best holiday for you, and our team overseas can give you the inside scoop on how to spend your time away with us.</p>]]></description>
