  <popularWalkingRoutes><![CDATA[<p>There are lots of great options, and it's tricky to pick our favourites, but here's a few options that we really love:</p>
<h3>Stari Grad</h3>
<ul>
<li>Easy walk</li>
<li>2.5km with 170m ascent/descent</li>
<li>Expect to take around 30-40 minutes in both directions</li>
</ul>
<p>For the most impressive panorama over Kamnik and the surrounding mountains, this walk is a must-do and is a pretty easy starting point to exploring the area. It starts in the centre of Kamnik town, and takes only around 35 minutes to reach the old castle ruins at Stari Grad - with information on local wildlife along the way, it's a great option for families.</p>
<h3>Velika Planina</h3>
<ul>
<li>Moderate walk</li>
<li>12.5km with 320m ascent/descent</li>
<li>Expect to take around four hours</li>
</ul>
<p>Slovenia's most beautiful mountain pastures, the Velika Planina is dotted with ancient shepherd's huts, many of which are still used today. A loop of the area, starting from the top of the cable car is a lovely way to explore the area, and you'll pass many huts and the Snow Mary Chapel. Views stretch for miles in all directions and you can refuel at the Zelenci Rob mountain hut.</p>
<h3>Kamnik Saddle</h3>
<ul>
<li>Moderate-challenging walk</li>
<li>5.5km with 1,364m ascent/descent</li>
<li>Expect to take around six hours</li>
<li>Terrain is steep and rocky in places</li>
</ul>
<p>This walk is on every locals bucket-list for good reason. It starts in the picturesque glacier valley of Kamniška Bistrica and climbs to the mountain hut on the terrace of Kamnik Saddle, between two mountain peaks. At 1,864 metres altitude, you're up in the rugged mountains here, and will notice the fresh air, peace and quiet - and the spectacular views in all directions, of course. At the right time of year, the Alpine flowers on route are beautiful.</p>]]></popularWalkingRoutes>
